@startuml steering_angle_to_clu_frame_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Steering Angle To CLU Frame Signal Flow\n(steering angle/manual command -> CLU steering frame render)

participant "Steering state / manual command" as AngleCtx #F4F7FB
participant "CLU\ncluster render owner" as CLU #E8F7E8
participant "Display seams" as DisplayBus #FFF4CC
participant "Cluster / panels" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Frame Inputs ==

AngleCtx -> CLU : Chassis::steeringAngle\nCmd::steeringAngleCmd\nscenario manual mode
CLU -> CLU : if manual mode\nangle = normalized Cmd::steeringAngleCmd
CLU -> CLU : else angle = Chassis::steeringAngle
CLU -> CLU : frame = (angle * 69 + 69) / 138
note right of CLU
Representative gating inputs
- Cmd::steeringAngleCmd
- Chassis::steeringAngle
- manualMode
end note

== Display Publish ==

CLU -> DisplayBus : Display::steeringFrame
note right of CLU
Representative outputs
- Display::steeringFrame
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

DisplayBus -> Obs : steering-wheel render frame /\ncluster visual readback

note over AngleCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Steering angle reaches CLU from manual or chassis-owned path
2. CLU normalizes the angle into the donor frame range
3. CLU publishes Display::steeringFrame
4. Cluster visuals and panels consume the rendered steering frame
end note

@enduml
